After a player crosses a checkpoint, they will respawn there rather than at the start line if they fall off.

We recommend adding checkpoints to your Round after any particularly difficult sections, or to create a 'point of no return'!

You can customise the width and depth of a checkpoint in its SETTINGS.

Add a new floor object by pressing the PLACE button, then dragging it out to the size and thickness you want.

Changed your mind? You can resize an existing floor by grabbing a corner and moving it, or by editing its SETTINGS.

In this mode, players race through a gauntlet, avoiding obstacles on their way to the finish line!

This type of Round must include a START LINE and a FINISH LINE.

You can rename your Round and adjust the rules in the ROUND RULES menu.

Some obstacles, like bumpers, platforms, and fans, can move along a path.

To do this, select a moveable obstacle, then hit the PLACE button and drag out a path for it to follow.

Try editing the object’s SETTINGS to customise how it moves!

Looking for a way to make your Round stand out? Most objects can be customised through the SETTINGS panel.

Depending on the object, you may be able to change things like its colour, how fast it moves, how hard it hits, and more!

Try playing with the settings for each object in your Round to see what effects are possible!

Everybody loves a good ramp! They can be drawn in the same way as floors - hit the PLACE button, then drag it out to resize.\n\nTry changing a ramp's SETTINGS to adjust how steep it is. You'll have Fall Guys sliding all over the place in no time!

This type of Round must include a START LINE and a FINISH LINE.

You can rename your Round and adjust the rules in the ROUND RULES menu.

Some objects can be turned ON and OFF by triggers.\nHighlight either the object or a trigger and press the LINK button to create a connection.\nTry changing the settings of the object or trigger to customise how it behaves!

Need to slow players down or block them off? Walls, edges, and barriers have got you covered!

Walls can only be placed on a floor. Just highlight a valid starting point, hit PLACE, then select another point to connect them with.

Need something more flexible? Edge objects can be placed anywhere and resized to your liking.

Want to keep it simple? Add a basic barrier to block the player's path. That'll show 'em who's boss!
